EDA_stat

Seunghoon Yang

2022-10-15

Through the two datasets, I would like to verify that Busan, Ulsan, Gyeongnam, and Seoul have regional variations in admission, employment, and maintenance of employment status of female engineering personnel.

Loading Datasets

The first dataset is for understanding the numbers and ratio of female students. It is imported from https://kess.kedi.re.kr/index.

The second dataset is for understanding the numbers and ratio of female engineers in the field. It is imported from https://kosis.kr/statisticsList/statisticsListIndex.do?menuId=M_01_01&vwcd=MT_ZTITLE&parmTabId=M_01_01&outLink=Y&parentId=D.1;D_18.2;#D_18.2

edustat <- read_excel("../datasets/edustat_.xlsx")
files_list <- list.files(path = "../datasets", pattern = "*.xlsx")[-1]
df_list <- map(str_c("../datasets/", files_list), read_excel, skip = 1)
industry <- bind_rows(df_list) %>% 
  fill() %>% 
  mutate( = c(rep("", 316), rep("", 320), rep("", 302), rep("", 294))) %>% 
  mutate_at(3:44, as.numeric)

Some Wrangling

edustat_seoul <- edustat %>% 
  filter( == "" &  == "")

edustat_gn <- edustat %>% 
  filter( == "" &  == "")
edustat_bsn <- edustat %>% 
  filter( == "" &  == "")
edustat_usn <- edustat %>% 
  filter( == "" &  == "")

edustat_sum_seoul <- edustat_seoul %>% 
  group_by(year, , ) %>% 
  summarize(__ = mean(, na.rm = TRUE),
            __ = mean(, na.rm = TRUE),
            __ = mean(, na.rm = TRUE),
            __ = mean(, na.rm = TRUE),
            _ = mean(_, na.rm = TRUE),
            _ = mean(, na.rm = TRUE),
            _ = mean(, na.rm = TRUE))
